Coming Home is the eighth episode of the fourteenth season of ER, and the two hundred ninety-eighth episode overall.

Starring: Goran Visnjic (Dr. Luka Kovac), Maura Tierney (Dr. Abby Lockhart), Mekhi Phifer (Dr. Gregory Pratt), Parminder Nagra (Dr. Neela Rasgotra), John Stamos (Dr. Tony Gates), Linda Cardellini (Nurse Samantha Taggart), Scott Grimes (Dr. Archie Morris)

Special Guest Stars: Stanley Tucci (Dr. Kevin Moretti), Reiko Aylesworth (Julia Dupree), Frances Conroy (Becky Riley)

Guest Starring: Grant Albrecht (Ronny Faneca), Charles Esten (Dr. Barry Grossman), Steven Christopher Parker (Harold Zelinsky), Deezer D. (Nurse Malik McGrath), Troy Evans (Frank Martin), Yvette Freeman (Nurse Haleh Adams), Chloe Greenfield (Sarah Riley), Bill Bolender (Hank Riley), Ron Bottitta (Lionel Hines-Kennedy), Hannah Curtis (Lionel's Girlfriend), Dylan McLaughlin (Marcus Faneca), Demetrius Navarro (Morales), Michael Rady (Brian Moretti), Simon Templeman (Gareth)

Co-Starring: Andrew M. Connolly (Brit #1), Brendan Patrick Connor (Reidy), Jacy Defilippo (Kim), Ethan Flower (Brit #2), Dinah Lenney (Shirley), Randy McPherson (Police Officer), Don Pugsley (Lloyd), Zoran Radanovich (Niko), Krystal Rohrer (Ruby), Dig Wayne (Dr. Berkely), Josh Wise (Rick)

Plot Overview

Abby's attitude starts affecting the ER staff; Kovac returns from Croatia a day early; Gates and Julia's tryst is interrupted when Sarah calls Gates for help; Moretti gets a phone call about his son and leaves work to be with him; Neela's intern makes her proud when he is able to handle a critical situation; Morris treats a British man who was injured during a cheese rolling event.
